Subject: [PATCH 033/174] =?UTF-8?q?PGCL:=20arm32=20PAGE=5FMMUSHIFT=3D4=20b?=
 =?UTF-8?q?oot=20=E2=80=94=2015/15=20pgcl-test=20+=208/8=20pgcl-stress=20P?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ASS?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

ARM32 PGCL boot with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 (PAGE_SIZE=64KB, MMUPAGE_SIZE=4KB).
All 23 userspace tests pass with zero kernel warnings.

Key fixes:
- FIRST_USER_ADDRESS: PAGE_SIZE*2 → MMUPAGE_SIZE*2 (was rejecting ELF at 0x10000)
- fault.c: handle_mm_fault PAGE_MASK → MMUPAGE_MASK (64KB round-down below VMA)
- free_initmem: raw L1 table scan (4096 entries) to find PTE tables in init
  section — Linux PGD abstraction misses second L1 desc per 2MB pair, causing
  vectors page corruption when PTE table freed
- fault-armv.c: pgoff shifts PAGE_SHIFT → MMUPAGE_SHIFT (VIVT cache aliasing)
- pageattr.c: set_memory_* numpages PAGE_SIZE → MMUPAGE_SIZE
- ioremap.c: ioremap_page and iomem_set_ro PAGE → MMUPAGE granularity
- mmu.c: early fixmap, devicemaps, PTE table setup for PGCL
- kfence.h, pgalloc.h, pgd.c, traps.c, entry-header.S, thread_info.h,
  irq.c, setup.c, smp.c: MMUPAGE/THREAD_SIZE/stack alignment fixes
- fixmap.h: FIXADDR_TOP uses MMUPAGE_SIZE

Also includes debug prints in init/main.c, binfmt_elf.c, workqueue.c,
arch_topology.c, fdt.c, initramfs.c, vmalloc.c, page_alloc.c, madvise.c
for boot tracing (to be cleaned up in a future commit).

Tested: qemu-system-arm -M virt -cpu cortex-a15 -m 768M, nosmp
Build: arm-linux-gnu-gcc 15.2.1, multi_v7 config + PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
